##"breathing fresh air is the happiest thing. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Reporter, Zhao Siwei, intern, Yan Caiqi, thepaper.cn

Cleaning Worker Song Yu encountered the largest amount of medical waste since she started working at the Shelter Hospital, after orders came to clear away medical waste from the cabin.

The accumulated highly contaminated medical waste is piled up in the extravehicular compartment. Clamps are tricky to use, sweeping increases the risk of aerosol transmission, and then comes the task of cleaning up patients'food waste. In an emergency, Song took the lead in picking up the medical waste and putting it into a garbage bag.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Cleaning Staff Song Yu empty the garbage will be placed in the corner

In the process, he and his teammates had to open the bag with their hands and bend over to avoid the surface of the trash. Filled with 15 large garbage bags, they sealed the high risk bags and carried them one by one to a medical waste treatment workshop about 800 meters from the North Gate of Hall B.

Masks and Hazmat suits are tight as a drum. When he finished the first bag, he was panting and sweating. Nearly two hours later, his ears were mask rope "cut, " raw pain, the body was wet with sweat began to cold, the medical waste was cleaned up.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Song Yu, a cleaner, shuttles trash cans around the cabin

Sweat wave after wave, people desperately lack of water, wearing a good adult diapers did not use. Two hours later, when he and his teammates re-entered the capsule, his mask was drenched and the risk of infection increased.

After this extravehicular, he sighed: "can breathe a breath of fresh air is the happiest thing. "

On February 8, as a staff member of Dongshan sub-district office in Dongxihu district, song volunteered to enter the cabin to carry medical waste and patients'household waste. At its peak, Hall B, where he works, has more than 410 patients. The food waste generated by breakfast and lunch is nearly filled with 16 large garbage cans and more than 70 corrugated cardboard boxes.

"It is their job to ensure that there are always more empty containers in the cabin, to ensure the timely removal of rubbish and to ensure the cabin is clean and hygienic. ".

For nearly a month, he and his colleagues have been circling the garbage in a daily cycle: loading it inside the cabin, taking it to the out-of-the-cabin transfer station, putting it on a garbage truck, cleaning it out and putting it back where it belongs. Before the shift schedule was optimized, they worked more than seven hours a day, "soft all over" out of the cabin.

Shelter Headquarters will clean up the division of labor and procedures in a timely manner, garbage cans have been increased to more than 50, they work only compressed to more than 3 hours.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A garbage can is placed in the corner of the interior of the cabin

"In fact, running a shelter hospital is crossing the river by feeling the stones, " Song recalled. At first, empty bins, which were not reserved when the bins were emptied, were replaced with plastic bags and corrugated cardboard boxes. Disinfection spray pot, large horizontal mop, large black plastic bags, disinfection facilities are gradually added.

"Life is hard, and any job is grueling. At least this job can give you exercise. " As she did not anticipate the intensity of her work, she did not bring enough laundry. His nine month pregnant wife, worried about him, packed his clothes and took them to her apartment downstairs.

Five meters away, his wife puts the case on the ground. "must pay attention to the protection, you are two children's father immediately, must have the responsibility. " The wife's voice from the mask came sullenly.

"Don't worry here, my precautions are the same as those of the medical staff. My work is all sorted out and I will take care of myself at home. " His wife was about to give birth, and he blamed himself for being at work or in isolation that day, i can't be there for my wife. I can't be there for the baby.
